    <h3>January 9, 2014, 4&#45;4:30 p.m.<br />
    LVCC, North Hall&nbsp;N258</h3>
    <div><p>Smartphones and tablets are an indispensable personal hub for many consumers. Flash memory is at the heart of this experience, storing a consumer's most vital information and ensuring quick application launching, fast interaction with the cloud, and rapid photo capture. Now, an emerging wave of &quot;smart&quot; devices promise to connect consumers to their favorite electronics and their personal data cloud, and offer consumers exciting, never-before seen possibilities for more personal entertainment experiences, business, social media and even health. This presentation will discuss the outlook for &quot;wearables&quot; and other next generation connected devices, and the implications to the consumer mobile experience.</p></div>
